rComments: Peter is probably the best out of any prof/TA I've ever had. He cares a lot about his students, and always goes the extra mile to help them. If you show up and show your interest, you'll be in good shape. Could not imagine TRN250 without all his sass, wit, and I guess knowledge too. If you have him you're lucky! (PS- get his life advice it's good)

Peter was one of the best/most knowledgable TA's i've ever had. He frequently made himself available outside office hours for help, he led really good discussions in our tutorial section, and has A+ comedic timing. His beard is also good. I will definitely miss his tutorial and if you get the chance to be part of his class, don't pass it up.

Peter is hands down one of the best TAs I had at U of T. He really loves history and knows everything ! He is smart, helpful and hilarious. I wish he was teaching an upper year class so i could take it. In order to get a good essay grade, take advantage of his office hours

It has been a pleasure to have professor Peter Mersereau as my instructor in HST 702. His lectures and materials are interesting and amazing. The course itself is book-heavy and there are a lot of readings, but they are definitely interesting and worthwhile. Great course, highly recommend it. Just keep up with the weekly readings and class material

Had him for WW1 history class @ Ryerson. Textbook reading was a bit heavy, but seminars were good, his lectures were interesting and his humour made them genuinely enjoyable. Definitely speak up in class if you want a good participation mark, and make sure to take notes. He cares about the class too, so don't be afraid to ask for clarification.

An absolutely terrible prof. I get so angry just thinking about it. I figured he knew a lot but wasn't good in presenting information but that's not true. His lecture literally outlined the textbook we needed, and all he did would spit out stats. Very broad, doesn't like to admit he's wrong. Can't answer Q's asked and seems to be there to get paid.
His dry, sarcastic wit made my first ever, and only, History class bearable.

Peter is such a gem. He made me like history- which is saying something. He's hilarious, engaging, and really knows the material. I wish he was teaching upper-year history courses just so I could be in his class.
Peter is fine. I had History with him. Essay mark was great too. Just show your interest.
